{"body": "Well, I don't have any authority to get it accepted, but I'd love it if this could be reconsidered. So thanks for the response!\n\nIt just seems to me that this is weird in exactly the way that Ruby (not just Rails) is consistently weird. If that's a bad thing, then we should all go use Python--or Java! But we like Ruby because it constantly surprises us by doing the natural thing instead of the simple thing.\n\nThrow anything at it, and it spits out a natural result. Delightfully weird!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6042267", "created_at": "2012-05-31T17:32:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3510#issuecomment-6042267", "updated_at": "2012-05-31T17:32:01Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3510, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jcamenisch", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/e38511fada092c4be4263f2acda1862f?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F43f5c32e3648b44b3a0c218b29087999.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/received_events", "gravatar_id": "e38511fada092c4be4263f2acda1862f", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jcamenisch", "type": "User", "id": 366009, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jcamenisch/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383593bd3543c15100fc63"}, "id": 6042267, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3510"}
